analysis: The documents relate to military and government personnel, including adjustments to military law, transfers of officers, medical care for Coast and Geodetic Survey personnel, leave policies for diplomatic officers, extensions of enlistments, suspension of provisions for aviation cadets, allowances for quarters for enlisted men, civil defense training for federal employees, and delegation of authority related to the Selective Training and Service Act. The documents generally focus on personnel management, benefits, and modifications to existing regulations during both war and peace times.
title: Government Personnel: Regulations and Benefits
